metadata.name: Attractors Bestiary #95
metadata.description:
2D strange attractors have always been fascinating. Created from simple formulas, they are capable of generating a multitude of stunning shapes.

This generative program randomly creates and compiles a multitude of variations of a given attractor type. As a bestiary would show a selection of monsters, this one exposes these mathematical beasts. Each attractor can be viewed in full screen by clicking on it.

The available attractor types are:
- Clifford
- Clifford Squared
- Estienne 1
- Estienne 2
- Bed Head
- Fractal Dream
- Symmetric Icon

Artist: Estienne
Dec. 2021

metadata.name: Celestial Collisions  #630
metadata.description:
Celestial Collisions  - The following series is an exploration of organic textures that embodies the way of a gentle breeze and the simulation of color pencils that randomly generates simple shapes. Out of 380K different combinations of the following combinations,
an endless amount of orientations can be produced from the piece of work.  

For the interactivity element, turn on the (a)toms and check the pulsar settings.. on the interval the atoms will go from being almost invisible to standing front and center. Sometimes, you may need to look hard depending on the various atoms. 

* 's' - save an image of the current state 
* 'a' - activate atoms

The piece is to be experienced by default at 1000x1000, however, have fun with the image. It will adapt to various sizes and create different images by whatever size you view it in. 

@generatecoll 2021

metadata.name: Earth #258
metadata.description:
This artwork builds upon the annual Earth Day animations I’ve been making since 2009. The particle system was written from scratch in vanilla javascript (a single 22KB HTML/JS file). The particles are constrained to the surface of a sphere and exhibit "social interactions" from which life-like patterns emerge.

Each animation will be minted with a randomly assigned color palette, energy level, particle type, and social behavior. Over 900 basic phenotypes are possible, with countless subtleties expressed per phenotype. There are a few wild rarities waiting to be born as well...

This work evolved over a three day creative sprint with fellow algorithmic artist Canton Becker. We think the Earth deserves a blockchain that doesn't blow tons of carbon. This animation pays tribute to the climate scientists and tech innovators who are working to secure our future on this planet. To that end, 10% of all proceeds from this project will be donated to The Coalition for Rainforest Nations.

metadata.name: Calligraphic #82
metadata.description: CALLIGRAPHIC is an exploration of a layered writing system where multicolored strokes are overlaid on top of each other to express new meanings. Each minted artwork's unique positioning, stroke combinations and coloring is determined by a random seed hash.

metadata.name: Hatchbeats #93
metadata.description:
Hatchbeats are endless beat generators.

After a Hatchbeat loads, click once to start the beat, and click again to hatch it. Once hatched, clicking will toggle the audio.

Hatchbeats are not drum loops. Each Hatchbeat continuously improvises bars based on its prototype. Prototypes are patterns of hits where each hit has some probability of happening in any bar. There are 3 high hat prototypes and 4 kick/snare prototypes.

Each Hatchbeat selects high hat, kick, and snare sounds from 76 possible samples which have 8736 combinations. The playback rates of these samples are modified for each Hatchbeat to create a virtually infinite number of drum kits.

Hatchbeat tempos range from 140 bpm to 200 bpm and come in several colors.
